{
  "stem": "13469.3",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And at that time, already, we were told that she was liable-- she was-- she had the potential of being exchanged against Germans.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And this is the first time that we heard about that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Whether my father knew about all this before, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But we were told that in a letter from the German officials, that Eve and her family might be exchanged against Germans which were interned in Britain.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "That was a big plan, which we didn't know about at that time.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But, again, I found out after the war that there was a big plan whereby the German foreign office, von Ribbentrop, who was the chief, he wanted to get all Germans back from wherever they were.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And he wanted to-- he didn't want to give up prisoners of war, British prisoners of war, because they would be fighting against them again.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the German plan was that they would give any other Britons and their relatives that they had within their grasp kind of thing-- and obviously, one that they would be keen to give up would be Jews and their family, which were of no use to the Germans anyway.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And if they could get Germans back, preferably German prisoners of war--",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they also, we hear, demanded two Germans for each Jew.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Or sometimes, the story was five and even 10 Germans.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So this is why, perhaps, we never got exchanged.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But that was the plan which this chap, von Ribbentrop, in the foreign office had.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And apparently, there was a big battle between him and Himmler, who was the chief of the Gestapo and the SS.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He wanted to kill all the Jews.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he didn't want to give them up.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
